## Context Bag

**LEXICAL:**
**H784 אֵשׁ (esh)** = fire (lit. or fig.). Primitive word. 549× in OT. KJV: burning, fiery, fire, flaming, hot. Derivatives: H785 (Aramaic fire), H799 eshdat "fire-law" (Deut 33:2), H800 eshshâh (fire fem.), H801 ishshâh (burnt-offering = "fire-offering"), H808 (foundation, from pressing-down of fire?), H861 attûwn (furnace, from fire). Note: H801 links sacrifice directly to fire — the offering IS a "fire-thing."
**H217 אוּר (ur)** = flame; the East (region of light). From H215 (to be luminous). Derivatives: H221 Uri "fiery," H222 Uriel "flame of God," H223 Urijah "flame of Yah," H224 Urim "lights" (oracular breastplate). Fire→light→revelation chain embedded in names.
**G4442 πῦρ (pur)** = fire (lit. or fig., incl. lightning). Primary word. 73× in NT. Derivatives: G4443 pyrá (concrete fire), G4448 pyróō (kindle/refine/inflame), G4450 pyrrhós (fire-colored/red), G4451 pýrōsis (ignition/smelting/conflagration/calamity-as-test), G4447 pýrinos (fiery/flaming).
**H6884 צָרַף (tsaraph)** = to fuse metal, refine. The VERB of fire-as-purifier. Used Mal 3:2-3, Zech 13:9, Ps 12:6, Prov 17:3. Derivative: H4715 mitsrêph (crucible/fining pot).
**H1614 גׇּפְרִית (gophrith)** = brimstone/sulphur. From H1613 gopher (cypress). Fire + brimstone = fire + fuel. Always judgment (Gen 19:24, Isa 34:9, Ezek 38:22, Rev 19:20, 20:10, 21:8).

**KEY: G4451 pýrōsis** = "smelting; figuratively conflagration, calamity AS A TEST." Greek embeds dual meaning: same word = refining (smelting) AND destruction (conflagration). The fire is ONE — the outcome depends on the MATERIAL.

**7 CANDIDATE MEANINGS:**
1. "Destruction/punishment" — Too narrow. Bush not consumed. Dan 3 boys unharmed. Refining isn't destruction.
2. "God's presence/manifestation" — Partial. Exod 3, 19, Rev 4:5 ✓. But Isa 9:18 (wickedness burns as fire) ≠ God's presence. Jas 3:6 tongue = fire ≠ God's presence. ✗
3. "Purification/cleansing" — Too narrow. Sodom wasn't purified. Lake of fire isn't cleansing. Gen 19 ✗
4. "Testing/proving" — Close but fails: Sodom wasn't tested. Nadab/Abihu weren't tested. Final lake = no test. ✗
5. "God's Word/Law applied" — Jer 23:29 "Is not my word like fire?" Deut 33:2 "fiery law." When Word contacts disobedience → destroyed. When it contacts obedience → refined. But struggles with "wickedness burneth AS fire" (Isa 9:18) — here wickedness imitates fire's behavior, not vice versa. Partial ✓/✗
6. "The consuming nature of absolute standard in contact" — What happens when perfect standard touches anything: it reveals composition, consumes impurity, proves purity. God IS this standard (Deut 4:24). His Word carries it (Jer 23:29). His law embodies it (Deut 33:2). Wickedness mimics it in reverse — consuming even its own practitioners (Isa 9:18-19). ✓ all contexts.
7. "God's holy standard in active contact — consuming covenant-violation, refining covenant-keeping" — Refinement of #6. Adds covenant dimension (the standard IS covenant). ✓✓

